"```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Hard: Reverse Integer (with Twist)\",\n  \"description\": \"You are given a 32-bit integer `num` that may be negative. Write a function to reverse the digits of this number and return it as an integer.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef reverse_integer(num: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Constraints\\n- The input is guaranteed to be a 32-bit integer, so the range of `num` is `-2^31 <= num <= 2^31 - 1`.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the reversed integer as an integer.\\n\",\n  \"code\": \"def reverse_integer(num: int) -> int:\\n    # Handle negative numbers separately to avoid issues with two's complement representation\\n    if num < 0: \\n        return -reverse_integer(abs(num))\\n    # Convert the integer to a string, reverse it, and convert back to an integer\\n    return int(str(num)[::-1])\",\n  \"tests\": [\n    \"assert reverse_integer(123) == 321\",\n    \"assert reverse_integer(-123) == -321\",\n    \"assert reverse_integer(0) == 0\",\n    \"assert reverse_integer(-123456789) == -967854321\"\n  ]\n}\n```"